Privacy Policy
Lighting&Sound America
believes protecting your privacy is important when using our website. We have introduced the following privacy policy to explain how we will collect, use, and protect your personal information.
Your Acceptance of these Terms
By using our website, you agree to
Lighting&Sound America
's privacy policy. If you do not agree with the terms of this policy either in full or in part, you should cease using this website
immediately
.
Changes to the Privacy Policy
Lighting&Sound America
reserves the right to change, add or delete terms of this policy at any time. You are advised to visit the
Lighting&Sound America
website on a regular basis to obtain notice of such changes.
Information Collection
When you visit the Lighting&Sound America website, you do so anonymously. Lighting&Sound America's website is located in the United States of America and is administered and maintained by
Lighting&Sound America
. When you access our website, we do log your IP address for administration and information purposes.
Our website may use "cookies" to allow you access to certain areas within our website or provide certain facilities. The "cookie" will never store any personal information you may provide.
We may ask you to voluntarily supply some personal information such as your e-mail address or postal address when making purchases or to enable us to send you mailings. This information will be stored on
Lighting&Sound America
's record and will only be used for the purpose that you originally supplied it.
We may also ask you to voluntarily supply some personal information such as an e-mail address to enable us to offer you services such as "E-mail this story to a friend". This information will be stored on
Lighting&Sound America
's record to monitor the service and will only be used for this purpose.
You may write to
Lighting&Sound America
at any time and request your personal information be amended or deleted from our system.
Data Security
Lighting&Sound America
is fully committed to data security and has put in place physical, electronic and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information you provide.
While we endeavor to protect your personal information, we cannot ensure the security of the information you transmit to us. It is therefore your responsibility to take steps to protect your personal data while on the Internet, which may include changing your passwords often and making sure you are using a secure browser.